&gt;I'm told that the other countries (especially the UK) consider the
&gt;EDU, COM, and like domains to have a .US on top of them.  I think it
&gt;would be a very good idea for us to do the same.

I wholeheartedly agree.  Such a move also provides other countries
isolation from our twisted domain machinations.  For example, if the
new .net domain went away, or a new top-level domain were created, it
wouldn't inconvenience foreign mailers, who would be dealing with the
.us domain server.  One problem with this, though, is that all BITNET,
UUCP annd other network nodes in the US would presumably fall under the
.us domain too, and I don't believe that there's enough coordination
amongst the various networks to construct a domain server that routes
mail to the proper networks.
